issues.body:
I'm using Spring AI in my project with a ToolCalling integration that streams responses via SSE. However, I'm unable to properly propagate these SSE events to the final client response.

Current Implementation:
I've tried using `returnDirect` with `@Tool`:

```java
@Tool(description = "count to infinity", returnDirect = true)
public Flux<String> countToInfinity() {
    return Flux.interval(Duration.ofSeconds(1), Duration.ofSeconds(1))
              .map(e -> e.toString() + ", ");
}
```

In `ToolCallResultConverter`, the result is always converted to a String:

```java
@Override
public String convert(@Nullable Object result, @Nullable Type returnType) {
    if (returnType == Void.TYPE) {
        logger.debug("The tool has no return type. Converting to conventional response.");
        return JsonParser.toJson("Done");
    }
    if (result instanceof RenderedImage) {
        // Image handling logic
        return JsonParser.toJson(Map.of("mimeType", "image/png", "data", imgB64));
    }
    else {
        logger.debug("Converting tool result to JSON.");
        return JsonParser.toJson(result); // Flux gets serialized as string
    }
}
```

Is there a way to preserve the Flux stream instead of converting it to a String? The current implementation loses the reactive stream capability.

Thanks in advance.
